Seems inevitable that Watson would win once they explained that it was being being fed the questions as a text file just as the question was being read. If you noticed the computer could ring in on every question and have plenty of time to pull up the response. Unfair.
I've always felt that the hardest part of Jeopardy is timing the buzzer. It's not really about trivia ... the questions are more-or-less answerable.

I think it's interesting that Watson is NOT parsing the audio for the questions and does not hear his competitors' answers. Also, of course, "he" doesn't have to prepare banal anecdotes for time-consuming Trebek bantering.
the day that computers are capable of time-filling banter is the day they will take over the world... or at least late-night talk shows
